usually takes weeks
of speech therapy.

353
00:19:12,819 --> 00:19:15,029
That is amazing.
Julian...

354
00:19:15,029 --> 00:19:17,197
So, she was exhausted.
I took her back
to the Infirmary.

355
00:19:17,197 --> 00:19:19,533
I needed to monitor her neural
activity anyway while she slept,

356
00:19:19,533 --> 00:19:21,744
but I still can‘t get
over that transformation.

357
00:19:21,744 --> 00:19:23,579
Yesterday, she was
silent as a stone.

358
00:19:23,579 --> 00:19:25,748
Today, she‘s singing
and laughing...

359
00:19:25,748 --> 00:19:27,500
You should have seen her, Miles.

360
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:30,503
How could I? I‘ve been
sitting here all night.

361
00:19:30,503 --> 00:19:32,546
Is it Thursday?

362
00:19:32,546 --> 00:19:35,883
Well, why else would I
be sitting here all night?

363
00:19:35,883 --> 00:19:38,385
Oh...
I‘m sorry. I forgot.

364
00:19:38,385 --> 00:19:39,929
It‘s all right.

365
00:19:41,764 --> 00:19:46,144
Morn caught me up
on how his 17 brothers
and sisters are doing.

366
00:19:46,144 --> 00:19:49,063
I‘d better head off.
I got an early start
in the morning.

367
00:19:49,063 --> 00:19:51,398
Oh, I‘m sorry
about the mix-up, Miles.

368
00:19:51,398 --> 00:19:52,900
Mmm.

369
00:19:52,900 --> 00:19:54,652
It‘s all right.

370
00:19:56,320 --> 00:19:58,656
I‘m happy for her.

371
00:19:58,656 --> 00:20:01,241
Happy for both of you.

372
00:20:04,120 --> 00:20:06,330
(<i> humming softly</i> )

373
00:20:07,707 --> 00:20:09,876
Sarina.

374
00:20:09,876 --> 00:20:12,962
What are you doing here?
How did you get in?

375
00:20:12,962 --> 00:20:14,547
It wasn‘t hard.

376
00:20:14,547 --> 00:20:17,175
Your access code
only has six digits.

377
00:20:17,175 --> 00:20:19,301
Is something wrong?

378
00:20:19,301 --> 00:20:21,179
I-I couldn‘t sleep.

379
00:20:23,430 --> 00:20:26,684
My nurse could have given
you something for that.

380
00:20:26,684 --> 00:20:29,729
I... don‘t want
to sleep.

381
00:20:29,729 --> 00:20:31,105
Why not?

382
00:20:31,105 --> 00:20:34,567
What if I wake up
the way I was?

383
00:20:34,567 --> 00:20:36,110
What if I can‘t...

384
00:20:37,653 --> 00:20:40,406
It‘s not going to happen.

385
00:20:40,406 --> 00:20:43,159
Your life‘s going
to be different now.

386
00:20:44,326 --> 00:20:47,038
Your future...

387
00:20:47,038 --> 00:20:50,083
is full of possibilities.

388
00:20:51,417 --> 00:20:55,004
You know, you‘re going
to be doing things

389
00:20:55,004 --> 00:20:58,674
that you haven‘t
even dreamed of.

390
00:20:58,674 --> 00:21:01,719
There‘s really no
reason to be afraid.

391
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:08,184
Sarina?

392
00:21:12,605 --> 00:21:15,149
(<i> sighs</i> )

393
00:21:39,757 --> 00:21:42,843
Good morning.
Morning.

394
00:21:42,843 --> 00:21:45,387
You didn‘t account
for the L-Two codon.

395
00:21:45,387 --> 00:21:46,847
What?

396
00:21:46,847 --> 00:21:48,766
That‘s why
the virus mutated.

397
00:21:48,766 --> 00:21:51,602
You need to target
the RNA transcriptor.

398
00:21:51,602 --> 00:21:53,353
Hungry?

399
00:21:55,022 --> 00:21:57,357
The L-Two codon...

400
00:21:58,442 --> 00:21:59,777
Of course.

401
00:21:59,777 --> 00:22:01,612
Why didn‘t I
think of that?

402
00:22:02,863 --> 00:22:04,698
Sarina...

403
00:22:04,698 --> 00:22:06,867
you‘re amazing.

404
00:22:06,867 --> 00:22:08,995
I‘ve been working
on this for months.

405
00:22:08,995 --> 00:22:11,330
You would have seen it
sooner or later.

406
00:22:12,706 --> 00:22:15,001
I don‘t know about that.

407
00:22:15,001 --> 00:22:16,627
Thank you.

408
00:22:16,627 --> 00:22:19,297
I‘m glad I could do
something for you.

409
00:22:19,297 --> 00:22:21,674
You‘ve done so much for me.

410
00:22:21,674 --> 00:22:25,178
